title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson 3913 as new in original box
postcontent:
I am offering a vintage Smith & Wesson 3913 with both factory magazines, in the original Smith and Wesson factory box, and it appears to be un-fired.  It is one of the earlier ones made, as it has no MIM black trigger or hammer.  It is stainless steel, with an aluminum alloy frame, making it a light weight, single stack 9mm.  It has a 3.5 inch barrel and the magazine holds eight rounds.   It is one of their third generation semi-automatic pistols that S&W refers to as a "traditional double action". This refers to a mode of operation wherein the first pull of the trigger is longer and heavier, and causes the hammer to rise from its resting position and then fall to strike the firing pin and fire the cartridge in the chamber. After the pistol fires that first time, the pistol is in what is called "single action", wherein the hammer stays cocked and subsequent trigger pulls are much shorter and lighter. The safety/decock lever on the side of the slide can be lowered which will (a) safely drop the cocked hammer, and (b) prevent the pistol from firing by disconnecting the trigger and by rotating a block between the hammer and firing pin. It is the firing pin block that makes dropping the hammer with the decocker safe, albeit somewhat unnerving. The original 3913 has been popular with law enforcement officers that need to carry their primary sidearm concealed. 
Asking $625, and shipping to your FFL is included.  Local sales preferred, with receipt and SC DL or SC CWP.  Let me know if you have any questions or need additional pics.

Also posted on other web sites, will remove posting once sold.
Thanks!
